This article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a visit to Mill Steel Company in Grand Rapids, Michigan. Pence praises the success of the company and thanks the employees for their hard work. He also discusses the Trump administration's policies on job creation, tax cuts, and support for the steel industry. Pence also addresses the approaching Hurricane Florence, urging people to take the storm seriously and offering support for those affected. He concludes by honoring the late Rich DeVos, founder of Amway, and pledging to continue working to make America prosperous and safe.